SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1123
By Hensley
A RESOLUTION to honor and recognize Geena Caprio, 2026 Top
Ten Senior of Lewis County High School.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to pay
tribute to those students who, through their natural talents and unflagging commitment to
academic excellence, have distinguished themselves in the classroom; and
WHEREAS, Geena Caprio is one such exceptional student, who was recently named a
Top Ten Senior of the 2026 graduating class at Lewis County High School; and
WHEREAS, through diligent study, steady composure during examinations, and
steadfast commitment of time and talent, Ms. Caprio has achieved outstanding academic
success and joined the ranks of the best and brightest students in Tennessee and our country;
and
WHEREAS, in her remarkable high school career, Geena Caprio has earned an
exemplary grade point average while participating in numerous extracurricular activities,
including concert band and the marching band, which she served as co-captain; and
WHEREAS, a talented writer, Ms. Caprio won the 2025 MLEC short story writing
contest; and
WHEREAS, Geena Caprio's display of intellectual aptitude and ambition surely bodes
well for her future success as a student at Middle Tennessee State University, where she plans
to study English with a concentration in creative writing; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Caprio's noteworthy achievement is a tremendous source of pride for
her parents, Philip Caprio and Angelina Sullivan, her school, and her community; and
WHEREAS, Geena Caprio's dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of the respect,
admiration, and commendation of the members of this General Assembly; now, therefore,
SJR1123
017658
- 1 -

BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we hereby commend and honor Geena Caprio on
being named a 2026 Lewis County High School Top Ten Senior, salute her impressive
academic achievement, and extend to her our best wishes for a happy, successful future.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
